gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 128, Trail Blazers 91
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeats Portland, 128-91. For Minnesota, Anthony Edwards led the way with 34 points, six rebounds, seven assists, and two steals aided by Karl Anthony-Towns recording 23 points, eight rebounds, and two blocks. Jerami Grant led the way with 20 points while Scoot Henderson tallied 15 points and four assists for Portland in the losing effort. Minnesota wins and improves to 39-16, while Portland moves to 15-39 in the loss.
